laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is hyperemic and enlarged with significant surrounding stranding and dilatation up to 19 mm in maximal diameter associated with a tip periappendiceal phlegmon/abscess measuring 1.8 x 1.6 cm. There is no frank free air.
Creatinine level is 1.7 mg/dL (normal range: 1.6 - 2.6 mg/dL). This result is within normal limits.
